Package ru.nsu.fit.smolyakov.tree

Class Tree<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ru.nsu.fit.smolyakov.tree.Tree<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>
    public class Tree<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<T>, java.lang.Cloneable
    An implementation of classic tree collection.

    While initializing, an auxiliary root node without value is created, so all nodes we add will be successors of this node or of successors of this node.

    Null-values are not allowed! add(T) and addNode(T) methods will throw IllegalArgumentException, and remove(java.lang.Object) and contains(java.lang.Object) methods will do nothing and return false.

    See Also:
    Collection
